"It is our mission to return Ukrainian citizens home," the report quoted President Volodymyr Zelensky as commenting. He added that he was happy for the sailors and their families. The crew of the Odesa-registered oil tanker Ruta were detained in Libya in 2017 on charges of smuggling petrochemicals. "Thanks to co-ordinated operations of the Ukrainian government agencies involved, a result was achieved in the negotiations with Libya and our citizens were returned home," the report reads.
--BBC--